data.setupjson-file#Setup.json file:
The Setup.json is the module contract. This file defines the needs of the module and its behavior with respect to the Developer Hub.In this tutorial the module will define some configuration in the setup.json:
A dynamic settings title of type string.
A label has been used with the key example-label-key.
Also it is specified that the module will consumed dynamic styles tokens from EDS Design System.
{
  "metaData": {},
  "context": {},
  "settings": {
    "schema": {
      "properties": {
        "title": {
          "title": "Title",
          "description": "Description, lorem ipsum lorem ..",
          "help": "Hint: Text next to a field to guide the end user filling it",
          "placeholder": "Placeholder ..",
          "type": "string",
          "default": "Hello React"
        }
      }
    }
  },
  "styles": {
    "service": "codeless",
    "options": {
      "type": "eds",
      "format": "json"
    }
  },
  "i18n": {
    "labels": {
      "example-label-key": "Primary color"
    }
  },
  "tokens": {},
  "services": {}
}
Note: When you build the project, you must make sure that this setup.json file goes to the root of the generated folder.

